turns.content:
each number represents an arabic pronunciation for example:
3anjad = anjad
zene5 = zenekh
m5alal = mkhalal

Ah, I see. In that case, "3inko janzeer bill beit" would be a way of spelling out the Arabic phrase "عنكو جنزير بل بيت" using this numbering system. In standard Arabic, this phrase would be pronounced "`inko janzeer bill beit" and it would mean "You have a monkey in the house."
